                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Colonel
                            <persName type="to">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-29">29 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1015. My main point was to get the SCALS under Chinese flag and control at the
                    earliest practicable moment, Reurad 92890.<note n="70" xml:id="d500fn70"
                        >Telegram of June 28, not printed.</note> In this connection your action has
                    met my requirement. However, it is still desirable to consummate the sale under
                    the provisions of the Ship Sales Act as soon as possible to avoid any possible
                    repercussion coming about through United States retention of title during this
                    intervening period. Even the loan of a United States ship though flying a
                    Chinese flag is subject to challenge as constituting support for one side
                    against another.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
